<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,330,431]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,330,356]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Thoracic dorsum with 4 longitudinal vittae, of which inner longitudinal black vitta is about 1/4 as wide as pruinose portion between inner and outer vittae on presutural scutum; abdominal tergites 3 and 4 each with a complete row of marginal setae in both male and female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption pageId="43" pageNumber="44" startId="43.[151,273,1940,1964]" targetBox="[182,1398,487,1930]" targetPageId="43">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,1940,2035]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
