<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,151,1522]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1458,1484]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species appears to be close to 
<taxonomicName box="[762,914,1458,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[762,783,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[801,914,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it in having narrow inner thoracic vitta, abdominal tergite 3 with a complete row of marginal setae in both sexes, and narrower cerci.
</paragraph>
